  "takeaways": [
    "This is a secondary comparison surface only: it excludes the combined TOC/ROW bundle from the treatment object to test how much of the current residual and strict-gap story is tied to that suspect block, without relabeling the headline treatment.",
    "At h0, excluding TOC/ROW changes the non-TDC residual response from about -72.74 to about -5.51.",
    "At h0, the strict direct-count gap share moves from about 1.04 under the baseline treatment to about 2.96 under the TOC/ROW-excluded comparison.",
    "At h4, the TOC/ROW-excluded strict gap share is about 1.35, which helps separate treatment-object-definition risk from missing direct-count channels."
  ]
